          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12845462/comment/14630781",
            "id": "14630781",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Rohith Sharma K S",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/New_York"
            },
            "body": "bq. Is there a way to launch application master on a specific host ? If we can not do this in a managed-AM-launcher? \nCurrently , launching AM on specific host is not supported. Any AM RR sent in submissionContext will be masked to ANY resource i.e any hosts in the cluster.\nYou can use node label feature to specify the hosts where AM . \n\nbq. is it possible to achieve this in unmanaged-AM-launcher?\nSince Unmanaged AM is not launched byRM, client can launch at any hosts in the cluster and register to AM.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rohithsharma",
              "name": "rohithsharma",
              "key": "rohithsharma",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Rohith Sharma K S",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/New_York"
            },
            "created": "2015-07-17T05:10:10.567+0000",
            "updated": "2015-07-17T05:10:10.567+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12845462/comment/15433835",
            "id": "15433835",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tdbaker",
              "name": "tdbaker",
              "key": "tdbaker",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Tobin Baker",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Vancouver"
            },
            "body": "We really need this for our application, and having to use node labels instead is a very awkward workaround (it can't be done programmatically from our YARN client, which runs with limited privileges). Instead, we make administrators manually configure the node label that the AM runs on, rather than have the application specify the AM location automatically.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tdbaker",
              "name": "tdbaker",
              "key": "tdbaker",
              "avatarUrls": {
